    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Columbia</placeName>
                <date>May 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1854</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I have made the following<lb/> collections for you.</p>
            <table cols="2" rows="13">
                <row>
                    <cell><persName>A Alexander</persName>
                        <sic>sett</sic> P Books</cell>
                    <cell>$18.00</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><persName>S Wolf</persName> Bible</cell>
                    <cell>9.00</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><persName>L Elias</persName> Bible &amp; Occident</cell>
                    <cell>15.00</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><persName role="author">I C Lyons</persName> “ “</cell>
                    <cell>15.00</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><persName>H Lyons</persName> “ “</cell>
                    <cell>15.00</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><persName>J Levin</persName>
                        <persName>Dias</persName> &amp;. “</cell>
                    <cell>3.75</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><persName>B E Levy</persName> “</cell>
                    <cell>3.00</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><persName>J D Mordecai</persName> “</cell>
                    <cell>3.00</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Sunday School <persName>Peixotto</persName></cell>
                    <cell>7.20</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><persName>L J Levin</persName> Occident</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rend="underline">6.00</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>$94 95</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>to C<add>?</add> Ship &amp; R Road freight &amp;c 206 Prem on CK 44</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rend="underline">2 52</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Bal</cell>
                    <cell>$92.43</cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p>for which I enclose you a check.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr. L Carr</persName> is residing in <placeName>Augusta
                    Geo.</placeName>
                <persName>Mr.<lb/> Jno Barnett</persName> in <placeName>Charleston</placeName> that
                latter I wrote<lb/> concerning his subscription to the books which he<lb/> declines
                taking giving as a reason the length<lb/> of time they were getting out also that he
                had<lb/> purchased a <sic>sett</sic> of books for his wife &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c<lb/>
                all of which I believe as much as suits me</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">There appears to be considerable blundering<lb/> either with you or
                the subscribers as to what they</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>subscribed for, for instance <persName>Elias</persName> said he subscribed for<lb/> a
                Bible you have him prayer Books <persName>Mr Levin</persName> ditto.<lb/> Then again
                there is dissatisfaction as regards the price<lb/> charged <persName>Mr.
                    Wolf</persName> wrote me he put his name down<lb/> for five or six dollar Bible
                &amp; others say the prices<lb/> are higher than the subscription list called for.<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Elias</persName> tells me <persName>Mr. Summer</persName> brought
                several<lb/> setts of the Prayer Books home with him for which<lb/> he paid 15.00
                for such as you charge 18.00 he did<lb/> not say positively they were bought of you
                but<lb/> were your books he says he would have no<lb/> objection purchasing a
                    <sic>sett</sic> but will not pay<lb/> your price. <persName>Mrs Levin</persName>
                says she will either take<lb/> a Bible or a <sic>sett</sic> of P Books I know not
                which<lb/> she was to have let me known which she would<lb/> take for the last ten
                days There are three odd<lb/> Vols of prayer books presume packed in mistake<lb/>
                could have sold the <date>kippur</date> but the price I asked<lb/> was said to be
                too high the average being 4.50.<lb/> I have on hand 2 <sic>sett</sic> P B. 27 ch. 1
                    <sic>sett</sic> $25 00<lb/> 1 Bible 12. 2 Bibles 8 ch 5
                    <persName>Dias</persName>. The balance I<lb/> have included in the <add>?</add>
                check</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr L</persName> &amp; the children are all well &amp; send
                kind<lb/> remembrance to you. All the children you have named<lb/> correctly but you
                have left out of the list the <add>?</add><lb/> child doubt much if his equal was
                ever born—his<lb/> name is <persName>Charles Henry</persName> &amp; you may think
                yourself fortunate<lb/> if his mother ever forgives the slight you have put on</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>him by not including him in the list <persName>Mr &amp; Mr H L</persName><lb/>
                <persName>Mr Levy</persName> &amp;c send remembrance</p>
            <p>As soon as any more money comes in I will forward<lb/> it</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Yrs truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">I C Lyons</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Pa.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
